<p>
<p>NADIA BOULANGER
<p>
<p>If you have built castles in the air, your work need not be lost;  that is where they should be. Now put the foundations under them.
<p>
<p>HENRY DAVID THOREAU
<p>
<p>The hand is the cutting edge of the mind.
<p>
<p>JACOB BRONOWSKI
<p>
<p>Our main business is not to see what lies dimly in the distance, but  to do what lies clearly at hand.
<p>
<p>THOMAS CARLYLE
