<p>
<p>JOHN BURROUGHS
<p>
<p>We should be taught not to wait for inspiration to start a thing.  Action always generates inspiration. Inspiration seldom generates  action.
<p>
<p>FRANK TIBOLT
<p>
<p>It is common sense to take a method and try it. If it fails, admit  it frankly and try another. But above all, try something.
<p>
<p>FRANKLIN  D. ROOSEVELT
<p>
<p>Do what you can, with what you have, with where you are.
<p>
<p>THEODORE ROOSEVELT
<p>
<p>We must cultivate our garden.
<p>
<p>VOLTAIRE
<p>
<p>He who has begun has half done. Dare to be wise; begin!
<p>
<p>HORACE
<p>
<p>If we really want to live, we'd better start at once to try; If we  don't it doesn't matter, we'd better start to die.
<p>
<p>W. H. AUDEN
<p>
<p>It is not enough to have a good mind. The main thing is to use it  well.
<p>
<p>RENÉ DESCARTES
<p>
<p>Action is the antidote to despair.
<p>
<p>JOAN BAEZ
