<p>
<p>WOODY GUTHRIE
<p>
<p>Anything that's worth having is worth asking for. Some say yes and  some say no.
<p>
<p>DR. MELBA COLGROVE
<p>
<p>Every human mind is a great slumbering power until awakened by a keen  desire and by definite resolution to do.
<p>
<p>EDGAR F. ROBERTS
<p>
<p>An idea isn't worth much until a man is found who has the energy and  ability to make it work.
<p>
<p>WILLIAM FEATHER
<p>
<p>The reward of a thing well done is to have done it.
<p>
<p>RALPH WALDO EMERSON
