<html><head><TITLE>Profile Faculty of Chemical Technology University of Twente</TITLE></head><body>
<H2><IMG  SRC=utlogo.gif ALT="">FACULTY OF CHEMICAL TECHNOLOGY</H2><HR>
<H3>PROFILE OF THE FACULTY</H3>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#main">Main areas of attention</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#depart">Departments</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#staff">Staff and students</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#graduates">Graduates</A>
</UL><P><P>

Within the Faculty of Chemical Technology at the University of
Twente there are three <A NAME="main"><B>main areas of attention</B></a> in research and education:
<UL>
<LI> chemistry,
<LI> processes and
<LI> materials
</UL><P><P>

The faculty is organised in so-called 'vakgroepen' which are equivalent to <A NAME="depart"><B>departments</B></a> or laboratories. In total there are 10 such departments each one headed by a full professor. <A HREF="/vakgr/index.html"> Overview of the research groups of the faculty.</A><P><P><P>
The Faculty of Chemical Technology has a permanent <A NAME="staff"> <B>academic staff</B></a> of 10 full professors, 8 part-time  professors, 13 associate professors (Universitair Hoofd Docent, UHD) and 28 assistant
professors (Universitair Docent, UD). The permanent supporting technical and administrative staff consists of approximately 90 persons. In addition, about 100 PhD students and 30 research fellows and post-docs are employed on a temporary basis. About 75% of these temporary positions are financed by external sources such as the National Dutch Science Foundation, EC-projects or industry. At present 750 students are enrolled in the first degree programme leading to the degree of engineer (ingenieur, ir). Apart from the 100 students in the regular PhD programme of
4 years, 50 students participate in an advanced 2-years course focusing on design aspects.<P><P><P>

<A NAME="graduates"><B>Graduates</B></a> from the faculty are offered many different jobs, mostly as researchers in a team concerned with new synthesis
routes, products or materials or in the development of computers programmes for automatic and continuous process control.
Graduates are also called upon in the design of plant installations or have an advisory or controlling task in environmental control management. Graduates find jobs after their studies in industry, research institutes or with various government bodies.<P><P><P><HR>
<A HREF ="http://www.ct.utwente.nl/index.html"><IMG align=middle SRC=homep.gif ALT="HOMEPAGE"></A> Homepage Faculty of Chemical Technology</body></html>
