<html><head><TITLE>RESEARCH GROUP INDUSTRIAL PROCESSES AND PRODUCTS</TITLE></head>
<body><H2><IMG  SRC=utlogo.gif ALT="">FACULTY OF CHEMICAL TECHNOLOGY</H2><HR>
<H3><A NAME="top">INDUSTRIAL PROCESSES AND PRODUCTS</a></H3>
<PRE>
Group leader: Prof.dr.ir. K.R. Westerterp

Scientific staff:
Dr. M.S.A. Vrijland                                   
Prof.dr.ing. G. Weickert
Dr. A.E. Kronberg
Dr.ir. A.G.J. van der Ham
Ir. H. van den Beld

Technical staff:
Ing. G.H. Banis     
A.H. Pleiter

E-mail address: 
<A HREF="mailto:k.r.westerterp@ct.utwente.nl">K.R.Westerterp@ ct.utwente.nl</A>

Phone: (+31)-53-4892879               
Fax: (+31)-53-4894738 or 4892479          
</pre>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#teaching">Areas of Teaching</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#research">Research themes</A>
</UL>
<A NAME="teaching"><B>Areas of Teaching</B></a><BR>   
The research group is highly involved in the compulsory and elective part of the curriculum with the following courses:
<UL>
<LI> general process technology
<LI> introduction to chemical engineering
<LI> project chemical technology
<LI> topics of environmental pollution
<LI> process economics
<LI> flowsheeting
<LI> optimization in chemical engineering
<LI> high pressure technology
<LI> supra-national aspects of the process industries
<LI> environmental chemistry & technology
</UL>
<A NAME="research"><B>Research themes</B></a><BR>
The research themes are directed toward applications in the chemical industry. Based on chemical and mechanical engineering, physics, chemistry, economics, mathematics, modelling and biotechnology several important areas in process development are studied, for the development of both individual processes as well as particular tools to be generally applied in this field. <BR>
The experimental work is performed in the High Pressure Laboratory and in a Biotechnology Laboratory. The High Pressure Laboratory has been selected for by the European Community as a host laboratory for post docs.<BR>
Research activities are directed toward a number of areas:
<UL>
<LI>improved processes for reactions with high heat effects to prevent thermal runaway in wall-cooled packed bed reactors, explosions in flowing gases and to control liquid-liquid reactions in semi-batch reactors,
<LI>hydrodynamics of two and three phase processes, like in gas-liquid (solid) reactors, for example the agitated tank reactor, the agitated slurry tank reactor, the bubble column, the slurry bubble column, the packed bubble column and the trickle flow reactor,
<LI>polymerization reaction engineering, specially directed towards polymerization kinetics of highly active Ziegler-Natta catalysts systems or metallocenes and (scale-up of) fluidized bed reactors for olefin polymerization,
<LI>fundamental study on (axial) dispersion in packed bed reactors, the influence of reactor pressure and the development of a better model to describe dispersion (wave model),
<LI>exploratory chemical process development for new processes,
<LI>process economics, feasibility studies and new methods for cost estimation,
<LI>computer applications in chemical engineering, specially process simulation (Aspen Plus, Hysim) and the application of model builder for chemical processes (Simu-Solv, Speedup, gPROMS),
<LI>biotechnology and environmental protection, specially waste water treatment using the bio-membrane reactor and biological soil decontamination,
<LI>automation and measurement in remote controlled high pressure mini-plants,
<LI>development of a multiproduct catalytic hydrogenation reactor for fine chemicals industry, which can handle a wide variety of reactants, heat production rates and selectivity requirements,
<LI>multifunctional reactors, specially the gas-solid-solid trickle flow reactor and the reactor set with interstage product removal for the synthesis of methanol and ammonia and the reverse flow reactor for the removal of volatile organic compounds for polluted air by catalytic oxidation,
<LI>dynamic behaviour of chemical reactors, specially the start-up and shut-down of reactors as a part of plant start-up and during process set-ups. This work is above all directed towards safeguarding of reactors and prevention of runaways during dynamic stages in chemical plants.
</UL><P><HR>
