<html><head><TITLE>RESEARCH GROUP MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGY</TITLE></head>
<body><H2><IMG  SRC=utlogo.gif ALT="">FACULTY OF CHEMICAL TECHNOLOGY</H2><HR>
<H3><A NAME="top">MEMBRANE TECHNOLOGY</a></H3><p>

<PRE>Group leader: Prof.dr.ir. H. Strathmann
Scientific staff:
dr. Th. v.d. Boomgaard
dr. ing. M.H.V. Mulder 
dr. ir. M. Wessling

Phone: (+31)-53-4892950
Fax.: (+31)-53-4894611
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:membrane@ct.utwente.nl">membrane@ct.utwente.nl</A>
</PRE><P>
<B>RESEARCH FOCUS</B><BR>
The research activities of the Membrane Technology group focus on three areas:
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="#prep">membrane preparation and development</A>
<LI><A HREF="#char">membrane characterization</A> 
<LI><A HREF="#proc">membrane processes</A>
</OL>
In all projects, special attention is paid to the relation of membrane material properties and membrane separation performance. The research projects are equally sponsored by the University of Twente, the Dutch government and European grants and by the industry.<P>
<B>CURRENT RESEARCH PROJECTS</B><BR>
Currently, about ten Ph.D. and two postdoctoral research projects are carried out. Below, the projects are listed by title per research area. <P>
<A NAME="prep"><B>Membrane preparation and development</B></a><BR>
In the area of membrane preparation and development research is conducted on:
<UL>
<LI>the formation of polymer membranes from quaternary mixtures consisting of a polymer, solvent, non-solvent and an low molecular  weight additive
<LI>composite membranes with glassy toplayers for  the separation of air
<LI>plasticization resistant gas separation membranes
<LI>pervaporation membranes for the removal of organic traces from organic extraction liquids
<LI>loose anion exchange membranes for the removal of organic acids from fermentation broths
<LI>liquid membranes for the removal of nitrate and heavy metals from  contaminated water streams.
</UL><P>
<A NAME="char"><B>Membrane Characterization</B></a><BR>
In the area of membrane characterization, the following projects are currently investigated:
<UL>
<LI>Characterization of the enhanced water dissociation in bipolar membranes
<LI>Performance and morphology characterization of polymeric and ceramic nanofiltration membranes
<LI>Characterization of polymer/penetrant systems with vibrational spectroscopy methods
<LI>Molecular modelling of diffusion processes in dense polymer matrices.
</UL>
<A NAME="proc"><B>Membrane Processes</B></a><BR>
The relation between membrane material and membrane process performance is investigated for:
<UL>
<LI>waste water streams stemming from washing processes and
<LI>the removal of VOCs from contaminated water streams.
</UL><P><HR>
<A HREF ="http://utct1029.ct.utwente.nl/documents/membrane.html"><IMG  SRC=more.gif  ALT="WWW-server"></A> The Membrane Technology research group server<HR>
