<html><head><TITLE>RESEARCH GROUP TECHNOLOGY OF STRUCTURED (TEXTILE) MATERIALS</TITLE> </head>
<body><H2><IMG  SRC=utlogo.gif ALT="">FACULTY OF CHEMICAL TECHNOLOGY</H2> <HR>
<H3><A NAME="top">TECHNOLOGY OF STRUCTURED (TEXTILE) MATERIALS</a></H3>
<PRE>
Project leader: Prof.dr.ir.ing M.M.C.G. Warmoeskerken

Scientific assistance: 
Ir. H. Gooijer
Drs. K. den Engelsen

Phone: (+31)-53-48930I8
Fax:    (+31)-53-4894821

E-mail address: <A HREF="mailto:h.gooijer@ct.utwente.nl">H.Gooijer@ct.utwente.nl</A>
</PRE><P>
<B>Materials Science and Process Technology of Textile Substrates</B><BR>
Textile technology is a field of interest in which different disciplines meet:
chemistry, materials science and process technology.<BR>
The research in textile technology is concentrated on the wet processing of
textiles and consists of two current projects:<BR>
<DL>
<DT><B>The application of chemicals in the foam phase to textile substrates.</B>
<DD>Foam technology, if applied in pretreatment, dyeing, printing and finishing has a favourable effect on dosing of chemicals, energy consumption and process yield. At the moment three-phase foams (gas-liquid-solid) are subject of investigation in generation-, transport-  and application phenomena.<P>
<DT><B>The flow of liquids (gases foams) through porous textile structures.</B>
<DD>In wet processing of textiles flow phenomena through the voids of textile materials are crucial for the extent of convection and conduction in transport kinetics in textile substrates.<BR>
The research in this field is aimed at prediction of flow permeability as a function of geometrical and structural properties of the textile materials involved. <BR>
The research is carried out in cooperation and communication with the TNO institute and a number of  industrial partners from the textile and related industries.
</DL><P>
As an advisory partner the laboratory of textile technology is involved in related research items of adjacent groups within the industry.<P><P><HR>
<A HREF="#top"><IMG  SRC ="top.gif" ALT="TOP"></A> Top of this page<P>
