</head>
<body>

<h2><img src="utlogo.gif" alt="" border=0 >FACULTY OF CHEMICAL TECHNOLOGY</h2>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h2>Course 132013: Environmental Organic Chemistry</h2>

<center><p><img src="orm002.gif" alt="" border=0 height=262 width=335></p></center>

<h3>Contents of the course:</h3>

<ul>
<li>1. Context</li>

<li>2. Air pollution. 'Greenhouse effect', <a href="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/ozone-depletion/top.html">the
'hole' in the ozone layer</a>, CFC's </li>

<li>3. Acid rain, soil pollution, 'chemical timebombs' </li>

<li>4. Degradable polymers </li>

<li>5. Life Cycle Analysis </li>

<li>6. 'Renewable resources' </li>

<li>7. To be announced</li>

<li>8. Closure</li>
</ul>

<p>
<hr></p>

<p>The next course will start in the 1.1 trimester of the 1997 - 1998 curriculum.</p>

<p>For further information, enquiries, questions and suggestions, etc.
please contact:</p>

<p>Hans den Hertog <a href="MAILTO:h.j.denhertog@ct.utwente.nl">(e-mail:
hertog@ct.utwente.nl)</a></p>

