</P>
<B>IMPORTANT:</B> When you want to ask something about a miniposter, please mail to the <B>adress at the top of the page</B>. When there is no adress you can mail to the ospt but <B>refer explicitly to the miniposter you are interested in!</B> (For example use the URL of the page in your mail)
<P>
<HR>
<P>
An important category of activities of the OSPT is not presented here but wortwhile to mention. Within the <A HREF="../2efase/index.html">two years graduate courses</A> industrial "designer/developer in process technology" which are organised by the OSPT interesting R&D and design results are produced which would certainly form a valuable contribution to these pages. However, for these one year projects often real life industrial cases are dealt with in order to promote the professional quality of this education stream. Consequently these results cannot (always) be published in open literature.
<P>
Prof.dr.ir. W.P.M. van Swaaij (scientific director)
<P>
<HR>
<P>
It is noticed that the OSPT is not responsible for any leackage of confidential information through the presented pages.<BR> It is the responsibility of the researchers theirselves to avoid such leackage.
<P>
Dr.ir. A.B.M. Heesink (secretariat)
