<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft</H2><HR>

The course process- and apparatus development is part of three postdoc courses of the <A HREF="http://www.tudelft.nl/">TU Delft</A>, the <A HREF="http://www.tue.nl/">TU Eindhoven</A> and the <A HREF="http://www.utwente.nl/uthomuk.htm">University of Twente</A>.<P>

The courses have some common characteristics. Emphasis is on obtaining and practicing skills for finding technical solutions for:
<UL>
<LI>design of products and constructions
<LI>design of processes to make these products
<LI>design of systems for transportation of people, information and goods
<LI>design of controlsystems, both for production and transportation
</UL>

Aspects that come up for discussion include:
<UL>
<LI>widening of the original training with elements of related technical disciplines
<LI>widening by emphasizing technological design in multidisciplinary connection
<LI>widening by addiction of science of industrial organization
<LI>widening by integration of knowledge and skills of multiple disciplines
</UL>
Besides widening of knowledge, deepening of knowledge in several technical disciplines will be necessary.<P>

The course lasts two years (3400 hours) and can be divided into four phases:
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="phase_a.html">phase A</A>: widening of basis knowledge (480 hours)
<LI><A HREF="phase_b.html">phase B</A>: deepening of relevant knowledge (640 hours)
<LI><A HREF="phase_c.html">phase C</A>: group design of processes and apparatus (600 hours)
<LI><A HREF="phase_d.html">phase D</A>: individual designproject (1680 hours)
</UL>

phases A and C, and the largest part of B will be finished during the first year. The individual designproject (D) can start in the first year, but will mainly be carried out during the second year.<P>

If you are interested you can send a letter of application to:<P>
Afdeling Onderwijs en Onderzoek van de faculteit STM<BR>
P. Kranenburg<BR>
Julianalaan 136<BR>
2628 BL Delft<BR>
phone: 015-2783659<P>

<HR>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../../pic/home.gif"></A> Process &amp; Apparatus Development School Delft

