<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Process &amp; Product Development School Eindhoven</H2><HR>

The <A HREF="http://www.tue.nl/">Technical University of Eindhoven</A> offers a processtechnology development course which lasts two years. Since the course started over 30 designers have been trained. In the beginning of 1993 about thirty students were still at work on the course.<P>

The course has the sub-title 'Process- and Productdesign'. Main point of the course is: <I>Besides attention for process design, attention for the relation between process, (micro)structure and functionality</I>. This must lead to an integration when developing, designing and starting up a processes for all kinds of products in the process industry.<P>

During the <A HREF="1styear.html">first year</A> of the course much attention is paid to the deepening and extension of knowledge. This is done by special courses. During the <A HREF="2ndyear.html">second year</A> a design has to be made.<P>

Goal of the course is to develop the intellectual faculty for synthesis and interdisciplinary working, characteristic of the work of a designer 'Process- and Productdesign'. The course has directed one's steps to the processindustry and prepares the students to functions in the field of processdesign and productdevelopment.<P>

Supplementary information can be provided by:<P>

Ir. J. Wijers<BR>
Faculty of Chemical Technology<BR>
Room FT-hal 1.30<BR>
P.O. Box 513<BR>
5600 MB Eindhoven<BR>
phone: 040-2473559/2472840<BR>
fax: 040-2463966<P>

If you are interested you can send a letter of application to:<P>

dr.ir. H.M.G.J. Trum<BR>
Eindhovense School voor Technologisch Ontwerpen IVO<BR>
Postbus 513<BR>
5600 MB Eindhoven<P>

