<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Process Development School Enschede</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<IMG SRC="2ef_logo.gif">

<HR>

The Process Development Course conducted at the <A HREF="http://www.utwente.nl/uthomuk.htm">University of Twente</A> is based in the Prof. J.C. Vlugter laboratory of the <A HREF="http://www.ct.utwente.nl/">faculty of Chemical Technology</A>. The group currently has 40 to 50 two year research assistants. The courses started in 1987, in co-operation with the <A HREF="http://rugch4.chem.rug.nl/">State University of Groningen.</A><P>


The course aims at providing a specialization to graduate students in Chemical Engineering and other allied engineering fields such as Mechanical Engineering and Physics. The duration of the course is approximately two years and specializes the participants in process technology with an emphasis on  process research,  development, design and evaluation, including economic aspects.<P>

The training is structured into two parts:

<UL>

<LI>A ten to twelve month <A HREF="1styear.html">period of intensive courses</A> by professors in different fields of Chemical Engineering.

<LI>An <A HREF="2ndyear.html">individual year assignment</A> consisting of practical work related to the process industry.

</UL>

The graduates get certification by the Royal Dutch Institute of Engineers and find positions in the industry,  governmental institutions, research labs and engineering companies.<P>

Additional information can be obtained from the coordinators of the designers training Prof.dr.ir. G.F. Versteeg and Ing. H.A. Akse.<P>

For more information and application forms, contact our secretary Nicole Haitjema (phone:  +31-(0)53-4894337, fax: +31-(0)53-4894774 or email: <A HREF="mailto:N.Haitjema@ct.utwente.nl"> N.Haitjema@ct.utwente.nl</A>.<P>

