<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Kinetics of a co-immobilised system
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE BORDER=2>
<TR><TD WIDTH=142><P>
<IMG SRC="uva.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH=539><BR>
<B><FONT SIZE=5>Kinetics of a co-immobilised system</FONT></B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=142><B>PhD student:</B></TD><TD WIDTH=539><B>Laura Hellendoorn</B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=142><B>Project term:</B></TD><TD WIDTH=539><B>1992-1996</B>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=142><B>Sponsor:</B></TD><TD WIDTH=539><B>UvA</B>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
An artificial biocatalyst particle containing
amylo-glucosidase (AMG) and <I>Zymomonas mobilis</I> was used
to investigate the pos-sibilities of co-immobilised cultures (Fig.
1). This system converts maltose to ethanol, according to the
consecutive reactions:<BR>
<P>
<IMG SRC="bpk21.gif">
<P>
<IMG SRC="bpk22.gif">
<P>
<IMG SRC="bpk23.gif">
<P>
Kinetic parameters of enzyme and bacterium
were obtained from batch experiments.<BR>
<P>
<B>Immobilised amyloglucosidase</B>
<P>
Glucose concentration profiles were measured
in agar beads containing different amounts of enzyme (Fig. 2).
Drawn lines were calculated using V<SUB>max</SUB> of the immobilised
enzyme and K<SUB>m</SUB> of the suspended enzyme. As theoretical
and experimental profiles agree reasonably well, it seems that
the K<SUB>m</SUB> value of amyloglucosidase is unaffected by immobilisation<B>.</B>
<P>
<B>Co-immobilisation</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="bpk24.gif">
<P>
Glucose concentration profiles were measured
in a homogeneous co-immobilised system in 
the course of time (Fig. 3). The profiles were
also calculated with an extended reaction diffusion model, using
the measured kinetic parameters. The difference between the model
and experiments may be explained by a change of the diffusion
coefficient in the outer layer due to the required coating of
the particles to prevent enzyme leakage.
<P>

<IMG SRC="bpk25.gif">

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 01/11/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
