<HEAD>
<TITLE>PhD-projects Delft 1996
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<CENTER><H2>Delft University of Technology<BR>
Research Group 'Process Systems and Control'</H2></CENTER>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

Process Systems and Control address the technical aspects of design and operation of
chemical plants as a system. The major objective is to develop models and methods for these
complex systems as a tool for decision making in design, control and optimization of
operation. The group has a tradition in heuristic/conceptual engineering approach as well as
the modern analytical/computational means to deal with dynamic chemical process systems.
Areas of research interest:<BR>
<OL TYPE=A>
<LI>Process Design and Analysis
Uncertainty analysis; Controllability and operability at design stage; Application area:
Heat integration, Crystalliser design
<LI>Optimisation of Operations
On-line use of chemical engineering models; Dynamic modes of operation; Advanced
control techniques; Plant wide analysis and control of production modes
<LI>Modelling Methods and Simulation Tools
Multi-domain modelling; Model validation methods; Modelling and simulation of
complex units
</OL>

