<HEAD>
<TITLE>Development of Electrodynamic Tomography System
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<H2>Development of Electrodynamic Tomography System</H2>
Research fellow: M. Machida<BR>
Sponsor: Idemitu Kosan Co.,Ltd.<BR>
Phone: +31 ( 15)2783568<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:machida@cpt6.stm.tudelft.nl">machida@cpt6.stm.tudelft.nl</A><BR>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>1. Background and theory</B><BR>
Electrodynamic tomography(EDT) has a
unique feature in its sensing, the detection
of the displacement current by the charged
particles. Though the application of EDT is
limited to moving and charged particles, it
gives directly the information of the
velocity and requires no current injection to
the process.<BR>
The basic induction model can
be introduced from Maxwell's equation.<BR>
Eq.-I shows the simplified form for one
particle with the assumption the space
current, polarization and magnetization to
be zero.<P>

<IMG SRC="1041.gif" WIDTH=500 HEIGHT=84><P>

<B>2. Electrodynamic tomography system</B><BR>
In order to monitor powder processes by
EDT, it is necessary to apply a Fourier
transform to deduce the information of the
movement of each particle from the signal
which is a superposition of the peaks from
many particles in sensing area. The three
dimensional electrical field created by a
charged particle was previously calculated
to increase the accuracy of image
reconstruction(Fig.- 1 ).<P>

<IMG SRC="1042.gif" WIDTH=500 HEIGHT=220><P>

The image reconstruction of EDT bases on
the lines drawn by the ratio of signal
strength between two sensors. The simplest
example of the triangular sensor system is
explained Fig.-2. Three data points give
two ratios and two lines, then the one cross
point of two lines in sensing region
indicates the location of charge.<P>

<IMG SRC="1043.gif" WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=203><P>

In this paper, only the highest output values
of each channel from DFT are used for
image reconstruction. The frequency
information from DFT are studied for
velocity detection and the accuracy.
The EDT system of 8channel, 10bit ADC,
i486 40MHz, 512sample/channel, 0.8ms
sampling rate, 32x32 resolution and a
simple algorithm of back projection (no
iteration) gives one image per every two
seconds(=0.5 fps.).<P>

<B>3. Furure works</B><BR>
The improvement on the reconstruction
argorithm is necessary to get the more
accurate informations.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 15/12/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
