</TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2>2.8E-01</FONT></TD><TD COLSPAN=2 WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2>n.d.</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2 COLOR=#000000>5.6E-01</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=78></TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2>o-cresol</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2>2.9E-02</FONT></TD><TD COLSPAN=2 WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2>n.d.</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=57><FONT SIZE=2 COLOR=#000000>1.8E-01</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
The effective distribution coefficient will be a function of a.o.
the growth (G) and the mass transferrate (k<SUB>D</SUB>):<P>
<IMG SRC="diepen4.gif">
<P>
<B>Conclusions</B><BR>
- molecular mechanics are effective as a screening method<BR>
- melt crystallization can be used in the cumene process for ultrapurification
of phenol<BR>

