<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Dilution and micromixing of a feedstream
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<H2>Dilution and micromixing of a feedstream</H2>
AIO-2: Ir. A.T.J. Groot [<A HREF="mailto:tgtcag2@chem.tue.nl">tgtcag2@chem.tue.nl</A>]<BR>
sponsor: Akzo Nobel<BR>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Feedstream mixing in polymerisation</B><P>

When reaction rates are high, mixing of
the feedstream with the bulk liquid may be
a critical factor in determining product
properties. In order to study the feedstream
mixing of a semi-batch polymerisation, the
mixing process is studied separated from
the polymerisation reactor.<P>

<B>Objectives</B><P>

Visualisation of mixing of a low
viscous feedstream mixing with a high
viscous bulk liquid.<BR>

Determination of dilution rate and
micromixing rate.<BR>
<P>

<B>Visualisation of the feedstream</B><P>

By applying a lasersheet through the centre
of the emerging jet, mixing of the jet is
visualised using a fluorescent tracer. The
fluorescence intensity is proportional to
the tracer concentration. High speed
imaging provides high time and space
resolution.<P>

<IMG SRC="2001.gif" WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=115><P>

Postprocessing provides time-averaged
axial intensity profiles visualising mixing
on a macroscopic scale (dilution) and on a
molecular scale (micromixing).<P>

<B>Dilution</B><P>

Bulk fluid is entrained by the jet and is
distributed accross the jet radius: dilution.
The dilution rate is obtained from the axial
intensity gradient using the self-similarity
of the velocity profile. Mixing the jet and
bulk at a 7:1 ratio requires 0.2.10<SUP>-3</SUP> s.<P>

<B>Micromixing</B><P>

The fluorescence yield is a function of
local pH-value (maximum yield at high
pH-value, low yield at low pH-value).
Therefore, micromixing can be visualised
by a rapid acid-base reaction altering the
local pH-value. By mixing a jet at high
pH-value and bulk fluid at low pH-value
local fluorescence intensity decreases by
dilution and by decrease of local pH-value.
As the contribution of dilution is known,
the contribution of micromixing can be
determined. Mixing jet and bulk on a
molecular scale at a 7:1 ratio requires
24.10<SUP>-3</SUP> s.<P>

<IMG SRC="2002.gif" WIDTH=350 HEIGHT=306><P>

<B>Conclusions</B><P>

A feedstream pumped into a high
viscous bulk behaves like a jet.<BR>
Dilution is 100 times faster than
micromixing in the feedstream of the
polymerisation reactor.<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 12/12/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
