<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The production of zinc sulfide particles suitable for CMT phosphors
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<H2>The production of zinc sulfide particles suitable for CMT phosphors</H2>
AIO-2:Henk Donkers<BR>
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:tgtchd@chem.tue.nl">tgtchd@chem.tue.nl</A><BR>
Sponsor: Philips Lighting B.V. Maarheeze<BR>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
Phosphors used in Colour Monitor Tubes
(CMT) require a smaller particle size, than
the phosphors made from the zinc sulfide
(ZnS) particles presently produced at
Philips Lighting B.V. Maarheeze.
Therefore a new grade of ZnS particles
suitable for CMT phosphors has to be
obtained.<P>

<B>Process description</B><BR>
ZnS is precipitated from an aqueous
ZnSO<SUB>4</SUB>-solution and H<SUB>2</SUB>S-gas in a semi-
batch process. Initially a stirred tank
reactor is filled with a alkaline solution and
brought under H2S-pressure. The ZnSO<SUB>4</SUB>-
solution is fed to the reactor at a constant
flow rate. The ZnSO<SUB>4</SUB>-solution is prepared
from ZnO and H2SO<SUB>4</SUB> and impurities are
removed. The H<SUB>2</SUB>S-gas is obtained from a
reaction between Nails and HCl. The
formed ZnS agglomerates are separated
and wash in a centrifuge, followed by a
drying process.<P>

<B>Experiments</B><BR>
The influence of the process variables on
the morphology of the ZnS particles and
the morphology of the phosphors obtained
from these ZnS particles is studied on
industrial scale. These experiments are
based on the results of pilot experiments.<P>

<B>Results</B><BR>
It is possible to produce ZnS particles
suitable for CMT phosphors in the present
production facility, by adjusting the
process parameters. There are problems
with the reproducibility, but only a few
experiments to determine the
reproducibility have been done.<P>

<B>Further research</B><BR>
To determine the reproducibility of the
CMT grade ZnS, more experiments have to
be repeated several times.<BR>
To determine the controllability of the
process, experiments with small deviations
in the process variables have to be done.<P>

<B>Process design</B><BR>
The particle size of the CMT grade ZnS is
close to the limit for the present centrifuge.
Therefore deviations in the process can
cause problems in the solid-liquid
separation. It is necessary to study the
present and alternative solid-liquid
separation processes.<P>

With the introduction of a new product and
an expected growth of the market of the
present ZnS, the demand will exceed the
present production capacity. Therefore
possibilities for the extension and/or
intensification of the present processes
have to be studied.<P>

