<HEAD><TITLE>Phd-projects Eindhoven 1996</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>CMT<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
Technical University of Eindhoven
Faculty of Chemical Technology
P.O. Box 513
NL 5600 MB Eindhoven

telephone: +31 (0)40 247 3024
fax:       +31 (0)40 244 3762
e-mail:    <A HREF="mailto:Denise@chem.tue.nl">Denise@chem.tue.nl</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<H2>Centre for Environmental Technology (CMT)</H2><P>

Prof. dr. ir. F.J.J.G. Janssen<BR>
<P>
<B>Status</B><BR>
The recently founded centre is an intra-
departmental working party between
several laboratories of the Faculty of
Chemical Engineering and Chemistry.<P>

<B>Programme in general</B><BR>
Over the long term, research and
development is the key to successful
implementation of environmentally
clean technologies. Research is needed
to improve our understanding of
atmospheric, terrestrial and aquatic
systems and reduce the use of energy,
materials and other inputs.<BR>
A sustainable development is based on
studies and know-how about issues
such as biomass-to-energy conversion,
biomass-to-feedstock, energy savings,
and the effects of emissions on soil,
water and air.<BR>
Gasification and pyrolysis will be used
as tools for the conversion of biomass
and other types of waste into useful
chemicals or energy.<BR>
End-of-pipe technologies covered
include gas and water cleanup systems
such as biological techniques and
electrochemical methods.<BR>
Life Cycle Analysis techniques will be
developed and used in order to find
technico-economically acceptable and
environmentally friendly routes for the
chemical industry.<BR>
Special focus is on recycling
technology development via a co-
operation with the Proefiuin Recycling
Initiatieven (PRI). PR1 is a co-
operation between the TU Eindhoven
and a number of companies busy in
recycling with the aim of developing
new ideas in the field of recycling.<P>

<B>Aims</B><BR>
CMT initiates, co-ordinates and
stimulates co-operation on
environmental technology within the
Faculty of Chemical Engineering and
Chemistry. CMT acts as an Expertise
Centre for the region in the field of
Environmental Technology.
CMT focuses its research on the
following themes:<P>
<UL>
<LI>Energy saving in the chemical
industry
<LI>Sustainable energy
<LI>Environmental chemistry and
analysis
<LI>Biological exhaust gas cleanup
<LI>Thermal processing technology
</UL><P>

<B>Permanent staff</B><BR>
Prof. dr.ir. F.J.J.G.Janssen<BR>
ir. A. Bieze<BR>
Dr. ir. H.G. Janssen<BR>
Dr. L.J.J. Janssen<BR>
Dr.ir. J.M.N. van Kasteren<BR>
Prof. ir. S.P.P. Ottengraf<BR>
Prof. dr. P.J.F. Sandra<BR>
ir. H. Zeedijk<BR><P>

<B>Research scientists</B><BR>
ir. P.P.A.J. van Schijndel<BR>
ir. M.J.P. Slapak<BR>
ir. K. Njau
<P>
<B>Research Topics</B><BR>
Thermal conversion technologies of
biomass and waste
Gas cleanup systems for these
technologies<BR>
Biological purification of industrial
waste gases<BR>
Thermal processes<BR>
Electrochemical Technology<BR>
Environmental Analysis<BR>
Solid Waste technology<BR>
DENOX research<BR>
Waste water purification<BR>
Life Cycle Assesment<BR>
Energy and Exergy of chemical plants<BR>

