<HEAD>
<TITLE>Modelling hydrodynamics of gas - liquid bubble columns
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<H2>Modelling hydrodynamics of gas - liquid bubble columns</H2>
PhD student: Ir. E. Delnoij (+31 - 53 - 4892405 / <A HREF="mailto:E.Delnoij@ct.utwente.nl">E.Delnoij@ct.utwente.nl</A>)<BR>
Supervisor: Dr. Ir. J. A.M. Kuipers<BR>
Project term: 1-11-1994- 1-11-1998<BR>
Sponsor: DSM<BR>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<IMG SRC="2371.gif" ALIGN=right WIDTH=175 HEIGHT=577>

<B>Introduction</B><BR>
Two - phase gas - liquid systems find widespread application in the chemical and process
industry. This applicability is mainly due to some distinct advantages of two - phase gas - liquid
systems. For example: two - phase reactors are generally very well mixed; resulting in excellent
heat transfer characteristics. One major disadvantage of gas - slurry reactors is the limited
knowledge about two - phase hydrodynamics and the problems arising in scale up.<P>

<B>Scope</B><BR>
This PhD project is aimed at reducing these
disadvantages of gas - liquid systems. Our first
concern is to model the hydrodynamics of a
gas - liquid bubble column. The resulting
models will then be validated experimentally
using Particle Image Velocimetry.<P>

<B>Activities</B><BR>
Two models are currently being developed; one
describing the homogeneous bubbling regime
of a gas - liquid bubble column, the other
model describes the rise of a single, large
bubble in a liquid. These models will be
extended to incorporate a description of the
solid phase present in gas - slurry reactors.<P>

<B>Results</B><BR>
The results obtained with the "homogeneous
bubbling model" clearly indicate a number of
features of gas - liquid bubble columns. The
dependence of the flowstructure on the aspect
ratio of the column is accurately predicted (see
figure on the right).<P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 15/12/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT25-B28-292</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA011-000115-B020-97</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://utct.ct.utwente.nl:80/~ospt/minipost96/ut/238.html 130.89.50.60 19970216181653 text/html 5067
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Sunday, 16-Feb-97 18:10:19 GMT
