<HEAD>
<TITLE>Recycling of Plastic Waste by High Temperature Pyrolysis
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<H2>Recycling of Plastic Waste by High Temperature Pyrolysis</H2>
Ph.D. Student: Ir. R.W.J. Westerhout<BR>
Phone: 053 - 4892935<BR>
Sponsors: IOP, OSF POWAM<BR>
Project term: march 1993 - 1997<BR>
</TD><TD> </TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE=0>

<B>1. Introduction.</B><P>

Large amounts of Mixed Plastic Waste (MPW) are produced every year. The dumping
and the incineration of plastics are possible methods to dispose of this waste, but due
to environmental concerns alternatives for these methods are being developed at the
momen. The high temperature pyrolysis of MPW is one of the most promissing
alternatives, but is technically not yet fully developed.<P>

<B>2. Objectives.</B><P>

The objective of this research project is the development, optimisation, technical and
economical evaluation of a process for the high temperature pyrolysis of MPW,
containing PE, PP, PS and PVC. The main objective of the project is the development
and characterization of the main process reactor. Reactor types, which are examined in
this study, are Bubbling Fluidised Beds (BFB), Circulating Fluidised Beds (CFB) and
Rotating Cone Reactors (RCR).<P>

<B>3. Results.</B><P>

The fundamental processes of the pyrolysis of polymers and the novel RCR (kinetics,
hydrodynamics and heat transfer) were examined and modelled. The RCR was tested
and developed further during this study. Our study have shown that the very good
product yields (ethene, propene and butene, see figure) can be achieved by the RCR
compared to BFB and CFB reactors. The economical evaluation of the reactors and
the pyrolysis processes showed that the RCR is very competitive with other reactor.
One of the main advantages of the RCR is that no fluidisation gas is necessary, which
reduces the use of utilities and waste streams substantely.<P>

<IMG SRC="2441.gif" WIDTH=700 HEIGHT=287><P>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 15/12/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
</HTML>
