<HEAD><TITLE>Phd-projects Enschede</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<H2>Department of Separation Technology<HR></H2>

<TT><PRE>
University of Twente
Department of Chemical Engineering
P.O. Box 217
NL 7500 AE Enschede

telephone: +31 (0)53 489 2921
fax:       +31 (0)53 489 4821
e-mail:    <A HREF="mailto:T.Reith@ct.utwente.nl">T.Reith@ct.utwente.nl</A>
internet:  <A HREF="http://www.ct.utwente.nl/vakgr/reith.html">http://www.ct.utwente.nl/vakgr/reith.html</A>
</PRE></TT>

<HR>

<H2>SEPARATION TECHNOLOGY</H2>

<H3>MEMBRANE SEPARATION MODULES<BR>
PRESSURE SWING ADSORPTION<BR>
CLEANING OF HARD SURFACES</H3>

<B>Permanent scientific staff:</B><BR>
T. Reith<BR>
I.G.M. R&aacute;cz<BR>
H. Bosch<BR>

<P>

<B>PhD-students:</B><BR>
E.R. Cornelissen<BR>
F. Foeth<BR>
J. van 't Hul<BR>
J. Mugge<BR>
J. Ophoff<BR>
S. Rekveld<BR>
R. van der Vaart<BR>

<P>

<H3>Research Themes</H3>

<B>Membrane Separation Modules</B><BR>
The objective is top develop membranes with improved separation features fort solid-liquid dispersions and solutions. New designs will be tested in industrial applications. Three research projects are currently in progress: Transport phenomena in spiral wound membrane modules, Recycling of process streams in the textile industry and Membranes separation in washing processes<P>

<B>Pressure Swing Adsorption</B><BR>
A program of three research projects is in progress: Measurement and modeling of equilibria and kinetics of multicomponent gas mixtures in microporous media, Preparation and testing of new 'coated' adsorbents and Development of design models for RPSA processes. The ultimate goal is to extend the present limited range of PSA applications<P>

<B>Cleaning of Hard Surfaces</B><BR>
The objective is to model the process of soil removal from hard surfaces in liquid flow systems<P>

