<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>COMPUTER APPLICATIONS IN CHEMICAL ENGINEERING
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<CENTER><H2>COMPUTER APPLICATIONS IN CHEMICAL ENGINEERING</H2></CENTER>
<CENTER>Dr.ir. A.G.J. van der Ham</CENTER><P>

GENERAL GOAL<BR>
Modelling, simulation, design and optimization of chemical processes as well as chemical
reactors using commercial software tools like Aspen Plus, gPROMS, Hysim, Hysys,
Speedup, SimuSolv etc., in order to obtain the technical and economical most feasible
configuration.<P>

EXAMPLES<BR>
<UL>

Some typical examples of processes investigated thus far or still under investigation, are:
<LI>Production of methanol using the RSIPR concept (reaction system with interstage
product removal) with TEGDME (Tetra Ethylene Glycol Di Methyl Ether),
Acetamide or other organic solvents as the absorption liquids.
<LI>Production of ethylene oxide: the influence of an increasing oxygen concentration on
the reactor and process design, and the technical and economical feasibility of the EO-
process.
<LI>Feasibility study for different types of heat pumps (eg bottom flash, top vapour
recompression and absorption heat pumps, and the absorption heat transformator) and
there application in chemical industry.
<LI>Steam stripping and air stripping of soils contaminated with organic compounds
(NAPL): modelling and experiments.
<LI>Industrial application of ceramic membranes and there economical feasibility. The
dehydrogenation of ethyl benzene to styrene is taken as a test case.
<LI>Regenerative, high temperature desulfurization of coal gas: a thermodynamic and
kinetic study.<BR>
First potential metal, metal oxide and metal carbonate sorbents for the regenerative
H<SUB>2</SUB>S removal were selected based on a thermodynamic study of the process. Different
regeneration routes were investigated. Second, the regenerative desulfurization
process, consisting of a circulating fluidized bed absorber and a fluidized bed
regenerator, using iron oxide as a sotbent was modelled in Aspen Plus.
<LI>Feasibility of high temperature desulfurization in a KV-STEG power plant (coal
gasification combined with a steam and gas turbine). The previous described user
module for a desulfurization process and a new model for the removal of hydrogen
chloride is incorporated in a Aspen Plus model of a KV-STEG power plant.
<LI>Recycling processes for ?VC, Polystyrene and mixed plastic waste. Back to monomer
as well as back to feed stock processes are investigated using different type of reactors
e.g. fluidized bed (Kaminsky), circulating fluidized bed (Batelie) and the spinning
cone reactor.
<LI>Technical and economical feasibility study of two hydrogen peroxide processes
(Anthrachinon process versus Arco process).
<LI>Development of a systematic method for selection of new working media for Organic
Rankine Cycles (ORC) for waste heat recovery.
<LI>Testing of commercially available model builders like Speedup and gPROMS for
modelling of various polymerization reactors.
<LI>Feasibility study of absorption heat pumps for waste heat recovery from flue gas.
<LI>Feasibility study of chemical heat pumps.
<LI>Feasibility study of adsorption processes for the removal of halogenated organic
compounds from waste water.
</UL>

<H6><CENTER><HR>&copy; OSPT - <A HREF="mailto:OSPT@ct.utwente.nl">OSPT@ct.utwente.nl</A> - last modification 17/12/96</CENTER></H6>

</BODY>
