<HEAD><TITLE>Process economics & cost engineering</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../back/tile2.gif">

<CENTER><H2>PROCESS ECONOMICS & COST ENGINEERING</H2>

Dr M.S.A. Vrijland, Dr Ir A.G.J. van der Ham</CENTER>

<HR SIZE=0>

Graduate students of the faculty of Chemical Technology as well as graduate students of the Twente School of Management are engaged in a variety of projects, all having in common that the $ sign is added to the process engineers' tool box of SI-units.<P>

<UL>The activities result in:<BR>
<LI> Technical Economic Evaluations of conceptual process design
<LI> Methods and procedures for establishing environmental cost
<LI> Optimization studies
<LI> Evaluation of new cost estimating tools and state of the art estimating software
<LI> Theoretical studies in Cost Engineering techniques
<LI> Predicting and shaping future developments in the Cost Engineering profession
<LI> Restructuring the professional education of Cost Engineers
<P>

Extensive contacts outside the university and active participation in industrial working parties and governmental advisory boards guarantee that the subjects under study are of more than academic interest only. The course in process economics as it is taught to senior students at the university has been commercialized, in the form of a successful yearly course for people from industry and government bodies.<P>

Recent publications:<BR>
<PRE>
<I>Bottlenecks in Cost Estimating for the Process Industries</I>
   M.S.A. Vrijland, A.G.J. van der Ham
   Proc. of the XIV International Cost Engineering Congress, Guadalajara, México (1996)
<I>Kosteneffectiviteit van aanvullende en vervangende (milieu)investeringen</I>
   M.S.A. Vrijland
   Onderdeel van het rapport Kosteneffectiviteit Milieuvoorzieningen, TNO/DHV/VROM (1995)
<I>Range Estimating</I>
   M.S.A. Vrijland
   Handboek Cost Engineers, DACE/Samson (1995)
<I>Computertoepassingen in Cost Engineering: Procesindustrie en Statistiek en Risico Analyse</I>
   M.S.A. Vrijland
   Bijdragen in de cursus Introductie Estimating, Dutch Ass'n of Cost Engineers (1995)
</PRE><P>
	
